.TH XMMS 1 "March 2026" "xmms-resuscitated 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xmms \- XMMS Resuscitated music player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xmms
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ files .\|.\|.]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B XMMS Resuscitated
is a modernized version of the classic X Multimedia System music player with
Winamp\-compatible skinning support. It uses GStreamer for audio playback,
supporting a wide range of audio formats including MP3, OGG Vorbis, FLAC,
WAV, AAC, and more.
.PP
Features include a 10\-band equalizer, spectrum analyzer visualization,
playlist editor, MPRIS2 media key integration, and Spotify playlist browsing.
.SH OPTIONS
Files or directories passed on the command line are added to the playlist.
.TP
.B \-\-playlist
Show the playlist window on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-equalizer
Show the equalizer window on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-dock\-playlist
Dock the playlist to the main window on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-undock\-playlist
Detach the playlist into its own window on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-dock\-equalizer
Dock the equalizer to the main window on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-undock\-equalizer
Detach the equalizer into its own window on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-shade\-main
Start the main window in WindowShade mode.
.TP
.B \-\-unshade\-main
Start the main window in normal mode.
.TP
.B \-\-shade\-playlist
Start the playlist in WindowShade mode and show it.
.TP
.B \-\-unshade\-playlist
Start the playlist in normal mode.
.TP
.B \-\-shade\-equalizer
Start the equalizer in WindowShade mode and show it.
.TP
.B \-\-unshade\-equalizer
Start the equalizer in normal mode.
.TP
.BI \-\-skin " PATH"
Load a skin directory or archive on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-reset
Start with default settings and an empty playlist, ignoring saved state.
.TP
.B \-\-playlist-menu-add
Show the playlist window with the Add dropdown opened on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-playlist-menu-remove
Show the playlist window with the Remove dropdown opened on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-playlist-menu-select
Show the playlist window with the Select dropdown opened on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-playlist-menu-misc
Show the playlist window with the Misc dropdown opened on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-playlist-menu-list
Show the playlist window with the List dropdown opened on startup.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B F5
Reload the current skin
.TP
.BR Ctrl + p
Open preferences
.TP
.BR Ctrl + l
Open the Play Location prompt
.TP
.BR Ctrl + j
Open the Jump to Time prompt
.TP
.BR Ctrl + e / Ctrl + r
Switch the timer between elapsed and remaining
.TP
.BR Ctrl + n
Toggle no playlist advance
.TP
.BR Ctrl + s
Toggle sticky window behavior
.TP
.BR Ctrl + d
Toggle double-size mode
.TP
.BR Ctrl + 3
Show file information for the current playlist entry
.TP
.BR Ctrl + z
Play the first playlist entry
.TP
.BR Ctrl + w
Toggle main WindowShade mode
.TP
.BR Ctrl + Shift + w
Toggle playlist WindowShade mode
.TP
.BR Ctrl + Alt + w
Toggle equalizer WindowShade mode
.TP
.B z
Previous track
.TP
.B x
Play
.TP
.B c
Pause
.TP
.B v
Stop
.TP
.B b
Next track
.TP
.BR Alt + e
Toggle playlist window
.TP
.BR Alt + g
Toggle equalizer window
.TP
.BR Alt + s
Open skin browser
.TP
.B Arrow Up/Down
Volume up/down
.TP
.B Arrow Left/Right
Seek backward/forward 5 seconds
.SH SKINS
.B xmms
supports Winamp 2.x compatible skins. Skins can be placed in:
.TP
.I ~/.config/xmms/Skins/
User skin directory
.TP
.I /usr/share/xmms/Skins/
System skin directory
.PP
Skins can be zip, wsz, tar, tar.gz, or tar.bz2 archives.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/xmms/config
User configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.config/xmms/spotify.conf
Spotify API credentials
